f_n(x)=\arctan{nx}
f(x):=lim_nf_n(x)
sup_{x>0}|f(x)-f_n(x)|=\frac{\pi}{2}\nrightarrow0
sup_{x>0}|\frac{\pi}{2}-\arctan{nx}|
0
\arctan nx
\frac{\pi}{2} - \arctan nx
\arctan 0 = 0
\arctan nx
\frac{\pi}{2}
\frac{\pi}{2} - \arctan nx
x > 0
\sup_{x > 0}\left|\frac{\pi}{2}-\arctan nx\right| = \sup_{x > 0}\left(\frac{\pi}{2}-\arctan nx\right) = \lim_{x\to 0^+}\left(\frac{\pi}{2}-\arctan nx\right) = \frac{\pi}{2}.
